# Documentation

When adding or changing features:

1. **Update feature documentation**: Keep the root README accurate for what the app is, who it is for, prerequisites, limitations (link [docs/product-audience.md](docs/product-audience.md) for non-goals), and short pointers—including [docs/getting-started.md](docs/getting-started.md) for build/run, first launch, screen-dump CLI, and extended operator tips. Put preset/show/palette JSON, `appsettings.json` structure, and NuGet dependency versions in `docs/configuration-reference.md` when those change. **The Spec** contracts live in `specs/`; `docs/visualizers/` and `docs/ui-spec-*.md` are stubs pointing to `specs/`. ADRs stay in `docs/adr/`.

1b. **New source files**: Place new or moved `.cs` (and project content) under the correct folder per `docs/agents/project-structure/` for the target project; tests mirror production per ADR-0064.

2. **Visualizer specs**: Update `specs/text-layers-visualizer/` (hub + `layers/<slug>/spec.md`); see `specs/TEMPLATE.md` and `docs/visualizers/README.md` (stub index).

3. **UI specs**: Update `specs/console-ui/**/spec.md` (hub: `specs/console-ui/spec.md`); see `.cursor/rules/ui-specs.mdc`. Regenerate screenshot and line reference when the number or meaning of lines changes.

4. **README vs. deep docs vs. agents**: When user-facing behavior or run requirements change, update README.md (summary) and `docs/getting-started.md` (step-by-step run/build/first session) as appropriate. When configuration formats, JSON examples, or pinned dependency versions change, update `docs/configuration-reference.md`. Build, test, format, and architecture notes belong in `docs/agents/` per topic—do not move that detail back into the root README. **Agent-specific** instructions (steering for AI assistants) belong in **`AGENTS.md`** and `docs/agents/` per topic, not in README.md—see [ADR-0068](docs/adr/0068-agents-md-vs-readme.md).

5. **Document deferred work**: Every "will do later" task must be documented. When deferring work (e.g. "will do later", "leave for later", "out of scope for now"), add it to an appropriate place: a task list in `docs/refactoring/`, a new or existing ADR, the refactoring README, or a dedicated TODO/backlog file. Do not leave deferred work only in code comments or conversation; it must be written down where it can be found and tracked.

Do not complete feature work without updating the relevant documentation.
